1� !Did you see where everyone went?
1�I can't believe they went ahead without me!I woulda expected more from Ulmia, at least!
1�Huh?They said they heard a voice calling them from up this way?
1�You gotta be kidding me! They can hear that!?I better find them quick!
1�Oh yeah, you better take this so you can wander around by yourself.Meet up with you later,  !
s!�What the...!?
1�Hey, what the hell's going on!?
1�And to me it promises...
1�Are you still droning the same old words, Selh'teus? I told you, we can...
1�Now what!?
1� , can you handle this?Think of it as a warmup for the main event!
1�Nag'molada!?
1�Whoa!
1�Hehehe...You did pretty good getting this far, Tenzen.To be honest, unlike you, I don't even want to get within spitting distance of him.
1�But that's what we gotta do.Right,  ?
1�What did he mean?
1�What the hell did he mean!?
1�Children...Promathia's children...?Does that mean...?
1�Resurrection and death...
1�I can't let that happen...!
1�Any attempt to escape from it is futile.
1�And yet it seems that some of you still resist.
1�But when you stand before the Keeper of the Apocalypse and behold the form of the Twilight God, will you then be able to withstand his call?
1�It can't be!
1�...Quickly, time is short.
..�Where could...?No!
1�Uh...He wishes to hear my song...The song that only I can sing...
1�I struck with the flat of my blade.They are not badly wounded.
1�Our companions were climbing over one another to reach the portal ahead.
1�Surely you have heard it?That voice has poisoned their minds.
1�To me it promises to teach the path of righteousness.
1�A path that can be walked without the slightest regret or hesitation.
1�?[Sir/Lady]  . Lady Prishe.I cannot go any further. That voice steals into my heart in spite of my greatest efforts to ignore it...It calls me to his side.
.!�What has he done!?
1�?[Sir/Lady]  . Lady Prishe. He has left the palace...
1�You are the only ones who can stop the Twilight God...
1�Power...Power to...protect...the weak...That voice...promises me...power...
1�Ah...A perfect law...where no crimes will be committed...lies ahead...It offers a new way of life...for everyone...
1�...He needs my strength to rebuild this shattered city...
1�Lady Yve'noile...I wanted to let you know...
1�We who are bound in darkness are soothed by your light.You can never know how grateful...
1�With the whisper of the soul I could have conveyed my thoughts to you completely...
1�Perfection...
1�I should be the one to attain perfection. I am the one who should lead the imperfect masses.
1�Why does the betrayer ascend to a higher form while I remain flawed and incomplete?
1�Tell me.What terrible folly have I perpetrated?Was this act so irreversible?
1�No...My path has been true.It is the incomplete world that is in error.
1�Yes!This world and the addled gods who created it have committed an unforgivable sin!
1�Lord Promathia!What do you want of us?What do you want from this world?
1�That's it, isn't it...?This incomplete world exists for the sake of imperfection...
1�That explains our existence...But I do not...will not...
1�Hm hm hm...Whatever is the matter, my brave companions?
1�Haven't you been dying for the chance to topple the Keeper of the Apocalypse? Why do you just stand there?
1�Come closer,  .Although it disgusts me to admit it, the only source of light here comes from the radiance that you and I share between us.
1�And I'm sure you want to find out more than anyone...
1�Your simple life as an adventurer has been turned upside down by these fools.
1�You have been constantly hounded by cries of ??Save the world! Save Altana's people!?? They have even asked you to die for their cause.
1�But you don't really care about any of that, do you?
1�You just wish to learn the truth. The truth that nobody can tell you.Am I right?
1�As do I. It is finally clear to me.
1�Are you sure?Maybe you have yet to realize it. My purpose has finally become clear to me.
1�Truth is the only bright point of perfection in this incomplete world. The only thing we can trust. Truth and nothing else.
1�Only one who learns the truth--one who holds all knowledge--can discover the perfection of Paradise!
1�Lord Promathia!Teach me all the truths of creation!
1�Then I will lead the incomplete people of the world beyond the gates to the origin of perfect truth!
.)�(We aaarrreee...!)
1�That voice speaks the truth!Our mother and father are waiting for us!
1�It says we can live happily ever after as one big family!
1�And we'll never be sad or lonely ever again!
1�I travel......hear lots...Hear...stories... Can tell...if...
1�Do you want to hear a story?No, thank you.Let's hear one.
1�What story would you like to be told?On second thought, maybe later.When Angels Fall(pt.1).When Angels Fall(pt.2).When Angels Fall(pt.3).When Angels Fall(pt.4).When Angels Fall(pt.5).
